verbose_text: In a study comparing olive (78% MUFA), safflower (78% PUFA), and palm (50% SFA) oils, ingested over 24 h, insulin sensitivity was particularly decreased by SFA, leading to a greater reduction in the disposition index, although all three oil emulsions similarly reduced beta-cell function.
